'''Lacus Lenitatis''' ([[Latin]] for "Lake of Tenderness") is a small [[lunar mare]] in the [[Terra Nivium]] region on the [[Moon]]. It is located at 14.0° N, 12.0° E and is 80&nbsp;km in diameter.  East is bordered with [[Lacus Hiemalis]], further north is [[Lacus Gaudii]], almost to the south is [[Mare Vaporum]].

No prominent craters are located in the lake but satellite craters such as Manilius U, W and X.

